option.name: LAST_COMMIT_MESSAGE
option.value: Implemented OS-check and native library loading in a bootstrap.

MESSAGE.value: Did some more basic work on the Server-application.
Logging is now implemented and works both to a file and on the GUI.
The configuration can now be set from the GUI and is probably saved and restored.
Did some work on the GUI-layout.
Implemented basic server-work. This does not execute any operations on the remote but works so far.
Re-implemented the MMR-Server with the Executor Framework. Also, the server now really shuts down immediately.
Re-implemented the Controller to use the Executor Framework and implemented a "Poison-Pill" to shut down the actions-queue when the application shuts down.
Implemented the native JNI-binding for Linux-platforms and got everything to work for now.
Controlling does now work from the Android-client application. Also made some improvements to the Server.
Implemented an address-book for servers (which is not yet used).
Improved the Server so all servers get shutdown when the application closes.
Improved the GUI, added a Logo and implemented the OSSwitcher (which shows the current OS).
Fixed a thrown "RejectedExecutionException" when the Server was stopped and then restarted.
Added a todo to create error-handling code so the button does not give the impression that the server was successfully started when it wasn't.
Improved the Log-component with a ScrollBar and auto-scroll.
Made DetermineOS a static utility class.
Removed the static-initializer which caused the program to force-close when the determineCurrentOS()-method threw an Exception.
Implemented OS-check and native library loading in a bootstrap.
